@MatheusAvellar I understand your point about characters not being the same width but overall I think limiting the string by character count is better.
It's simpler to implement and would make it easier to implement a better way to truncate strings by removing characters from the middle.
I think it's better to show the beginning and end of string (including extension) than cut off the end.
I.e. "very long name.pdf" would be truncated as "very...name.pdf" and not "very lon..." (of course the max length would be much longer, say 32 characters.
Have you checked how other programs on Windows (e.g. Notepad++ or Adobe Reader) handle this?
@Qynklee a pop-up to show full name would be nice but I don't believe this is easy to implement. I think that to implement such behavior we would have to implement fully custom menu, which is a lot of work.

